node.text:
@natashanic 💐 ❤️ 

VD: A series of clips of @natashanic ‘s mom putting on roller skates. You can hear laughing cheering and a bit of conversation muffled in the background as music plays over the video. The mom and daughter duo is skating around on a blue ramp doing standing tricks and poses together while helping one another with a hand. The mom tries out skating on the ramp transition and then at the end taking her skates off. There are white captions over the video that read “” when your mom puts on skates... for the first time in years...many years. And She doesn’t even skip a beat! She even teaches you a trick or two...she takes a run on the mini! Yup still got it! Happy Mother’s Day!

node.text:
In today's video, @kianayouwanna announces the winners of February & March Moxi Skate Daily winners as well as some updates to the challenge. It has been such a wonderful time to watch everyone participate in this & see everyones progressions, passion, the friendships they have built & so much more that comes with Moxi Skate Daily. What has been your favorite parts about participating in this challenge so far? Tell us in the comments below! 

Winners from February: 
Instagram: @sk8.bagel
TikTok: Mandimortem 

Winners from March: 
Instagram: @veebeerollin
Tiktok: Toestops

We have a few updates: To participate every month in the prizes specifically we will be picking 1 winner from each TikTok & Instagram & picking from the hashtag of #202funday30 to choose these winners. There will be two winners every month. We will check to make sure that you have been skating at least 30 days so make sure you use the hashtags & post your videos on a feed. Unfortunately we can not track them if they are only in your stories. 

With feedback from the community we can understand that it is not accessible for all to skate every day. We have adjusted the rules on how to enter for prizes by allowing you to start whenever you would like, but to participate you must enter by skating at least 30 days this year, post about it while using the hashtag #202funday#1, #202funday#2 etc etc until 202funday30 and on! (This was a required # from the beginning) and #moxiskatedaily 

 We encourage you to keep on continuing the days that you skate because it is amazing to see how many days you can skate in the year & the progression that you accomplish in doing so! We will still be awarding a winner for the full year once we end 2021! So we encourage you to keep going until  #202funday365 ! We will throw in some extra fun prizes for bigger milestones, any inspirations that we see in the skate world or just for fun they just won’t be every month. So we encourage you to continue to skate! 

Check back at the beginning of May to find out the Winners for April!

Video description in the comments!

#MoxiSkateDaily #202funday30

#MOXISKATEDAILY is the original 365 Days of Skate Challenge 

The challenge is extremely rewarding, positive, motivating and creates harmony and excitement in our community through participation. 

Participants stay connected throughout the year by virtually encouraging daily roller skating through video posts AND we meet lots of friends while doing it!

While following along in the contest by checking the hashtags we become inspired by the improving skaters that seem to blossom like beautiful flowers throughout the year! 

Here are the rules!

1. Roller Skate every single day and take a video or make an edit of video clips taken from the same day 

2. Post your daily video from that day to your Instagram OR TikTok feed, or both. 

3.  In the description of the video post, use #MOXISKATEDAILY and also #202FUNday1 to represent the corresponding day you are  on 

For example.... on your first day, January 1st, you will use #202FUNday1 and on Day 2 you will use #202FUNday2 and on Day 180.you will use #202FUNday180

4. You must be wearing and moving on your roller skates in your video post

5.  To win the GRAND PRIZE you must start January 1st, even if you are waiting for skates. For milestone winners, you can start on any day. So long as you are participating, you can win a prize throughout the year on a milestone day. Milestone days are not limited to 30 days, 60 days, 90 days and 180 days. There may be random milestone days, so KEEP SKATING! 

On milestone days throughout the year we will be giving away Camp Tickets, Pairs of Roller Skates and limited edition items to participants and on the last day we award a GRAND PRIZE (to a random winner who posted every single for day for 356 days). 

Our only ask is that you DO NOT CHEAT by stacking clips and posting later while using the hashtags. 

We hope this contest brings a momentous motivation that will IMPROVE YOUR SKATING and get you. STOKED ON YOUR PROGRESS and INSPIRED BY THE PROGRESS OF OTHERS and to CONNECT YOU TO THE ROLLER SKATING COMMUNITY! 

Thank you again for all of your patience, support, open mindedness and well wishes. 

We wish you the very best this NEW YEAR's HOLIDAY!

Sometimes as skaters and soon to be skaters, it’s hard to find the information we need. We slide into each other’s dms and email customer service, but that’s just not enough! Sometimes, we just need someone to talk to....

Well, everyone at Moxi is here to help and you will be helping Moxi to employ skaters with a special service we are offering! 

Next month you’ll be able to book a session with a skater that’s been trained in hardware, boots, skate set ups and maintenence of your roller skates! Even if we don’t have skates, we’ll give you advice on your dream set up so you know what to get elsewhere. We want you to be educated on what you need to stay rolling or get rolling! 

Reserve a one on one 20min call with a skater for $20. They can help you with recommendations from the tip of your toe stop to the top of your helmet! Link in bio to book yours!

While it may look like a mixup, it’s actually the best decision ever!

@estrojen Bowl Bombers now come in single color 4-packs so you can get the color you want! 

These wheels are 101A and 62mm with their smoothest roll at the skatepark, on concrete or wood. 

You can grab a full set in your favorite color now at moxiskates.com 

VD: A reel video of @kianayouwanna (they/them) tripping, throwing colorful roller skate wheels in the air, cleaning them up and walking away with a mistake gone right. Kiana is Black & White, Non-Binary, has short curly dark brown and turquoise hair, black eyeliner on  their face, tattoos on their arms and legs & light tan skin. Kiana is wearing a Black Moxi Mask, turquoise snake earrings, a black and a white striped crop top underneath a black romper. There is fun music playing during the reel. 

#EstroBowlBombers #Estrowheels #Estrojenbowlbombers #SolidColorRollerSkateWheels #RollerSkateWheels

GIVEAWAY!!!!

Do YOU have a new Moxi Romper? Well right on! We are so ecstatic about the comfort, durability and style of the Moxi Rompers that we want to give 5 people something special that will pair nicely with the outfit! 

We are giving away 5 pairs of the new Moxi x Skater Sock colors in the 19 inch length! All you have to do is use #MoxiRomper and post a picture or video of yourself in your Ready to Roll Romper. Make sure this is a feed post and that your account is on public so we can see! 

We will randomly select 5 winners on Monday August 30th in our Instagram story! 

This giveaway starts NOW! We can't wait to see how you dress up in your Ready to Roll Romper! 

Rules to enter: 
🛼Must be a feed post, not a reel, not an IGTV post and not a story post.
🛼Must use #MoxiRomper in your caption
🛼Must be above 18 or older to participate
🛼Must live in the US to participate
🛼Must message us back via Instagram direct messages within 24 hours to claim your prize 

Winner announced on August 30th between 9am - 5pm PST time on the Moxi Roller Skates Instagram story. Prize will be delivered via USPS mail & the socks and shipping are free!

This giveaway is hosted by Moxi Roller Skates and it is in no way sponsored or administered by Instagram

ID: A reel video of @kianayouwanna (they/them) sharing details on how to win a giveaway prize. Kiana is Black & White, Non-Binary, has short curly dark brown and turquoise hair, black eyeliner one their face, tattoos on their arms and legs & light tan skin. Kiana is standing in the middle of the frame with a pink backdrop behind them. Kiana is wearing a Black Moxi Mask, turquoise snake earrings, a black and a white striped crop top underneath a black romper. During the reel two Moxi Soxi puppets come up to help explain the giveaway details as well. They are white socks with 3 colorful horizontal stripes on the end & goggly eyes. There is text on the reel at the lower bottoms of the screen captioning the voice over in the video. 

#MoxiGiveaway #MoxiRomper #ReadyToRollRomper

node.text:
@myomy_tv rolling through in his Green Apple Lolly Skates with an impressively long shoot the Duck 🦆 

Lolly Outdoor Complete in Green Apple are in stock in sizes 4, 7, and 8 at moxiskates.com 🛼🍏

VD: A video of Myo (he/they) skating down a road and doing the roller skate move shoot the Duck. Shooting the duck is where you balance on one foot with the other extended in front of you while squared low to the ground. Myo has a clean shaven head and a black beard. He is wearing a grey, green and pink floral button up, black jean shorts, black socks and green roller skates. Upbeat fun music plays in the background of the video. 

#MoxiGreenApple #MoxiLolly #GreenRollerSkates

#MoxiLolly #GreenRollerSkate #MoxiGreenApple
